1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "To work with directory servers which lack transactional semantics, and also to avoid compromising performance of a normal Infranet system operation, Infranet propagates changes to the directory server asynchronously using channel objects. The channels are used to track changes to various classes grouped together functionally. A pre-defined set of channel objects are loaded from the init_objects.source file and are used by the PCM_OP_CHANNEL_PUSH and PCM_OP_CHANNEL_SYNC opcodes in the LDAP manager"
