1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/channel_event"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "To work with directory servers which lack transactional semantics, and also to avoid compromising performance of a normal Infranet system operation, Infranet propagates changes to the directory server asynchronously using channeland channel_event objects. Channels events are used to track changes to infranet objects individually. A channel_event object is created for each tracked change and is pushed into the the channel_event table by the PCM_OP_CHANNEL_PUSH opcode. These entries are consumed by the PCM_OP_CHANNEL_SYNC opcode in the LDAP manager."
