1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/data/sequence"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "A singleton configuration object of this class is used to maintain various sequence number generators used by the system to stamp bills, items etc. with unique and usually monotonically increasing identifiers. This is also used to generate transaction ids for correlating information with external system like payment engines. A predefined instance is loaded from init_objects.source during installation. It is recommended that you configure the various sequence number formats only once. You may define additional sequences for your use by using element ids greater than 1000000 or  you may define other sequence objects with poid id."
1     PIN_FLD_READ_ACCESS     STR [0] "Global"
1     PIN_FLD_WRITE_ACCESS    STR [0] "Global"
1     PIN_FLD_ACTION          STR [0] "ADD"
0 PIN_FLD_OBJ_DESC      ARRAY [152] allocated 20, used 5
1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/data/trial_bill_sequence"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "A singleton configuration object of this class is used to maintain the subords trial bill run count. This will be used by the parent trial bill run to pick the subordinates invoices. In case of multiple trial bill run of subords, before trial bill run of the parent, more than one set of subord invoices will be generated. During parent trial bill run, this sequence number will be used to pick the latest subord invoices."
1     PIN_FLD_READ_ACCESS     STR [0] "Global"
1     PIN_FLD_WRITE_ACCESS    STR [0] "Global"
1     PIN_FLD_ACTION          STR [0] "ADD"
0 PIN_FLD_OBJ_DESC      ARRAY [153] allocated 20, used 5
1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/data/sequence_lock"
1     PIN_FLD_READ_ACCESS     STR [0] "Self"
1     PIN_FLD_WRITE_ACCESS    STR [0] "Self"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "Reserved for internal use only.  Each object for this storable-class correlates to the database mechanism for allocating new poid_id0 values.  It is specifically used to support retrieving a range of poid_id0 values; it uses the object with the 'name' of the database sequence to hold a lock on the record when making alterations to the sequence.  Consequently, there should be one object for each poid_id0-generating sequence in the database which supports range retrieval."
1     PIN_FLD_ACTION          STR [0] "ADD"
0 PIN_FLD_OBJ_DESC      ARRAY [154] allocated 41, used 26
1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/deal"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "A deal is a package of related products. Packaging products into deals simplifies the price list as it is presented to the customer. A product may appear in multiple deals. Deals may be used to apply special discounts to products and also to restrict the start and end dates for the products. For example, you might offer a reduced monthly fee for a product if purchased by a certain date. Using deals adds flexibility to your pricing structure without requiring you to redefine rates and products. An account may own only one deal whose purchase level is set to 'all accounts and no services'.  Also, a deal must contain only products that confirm to the deal's purchase level. See also /plan and /product definitions."
