1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/group/plan_list"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "A plan list is a set of plans that you offer your customers when they register for an account. A plan list is set up using /group/plan_list objects. A plan isn't available to your customers until you add it to your plan list.  The plan list doesn't have to include all of your plans. You can create plans and not include them in a plan list until you need them. Or, you can offer one set of plans to one group of potential customers, and another group of plans to another group.  When you create a plan list, you designate which plans are available at customer registration, and which plans can be purchased only after registration.  PIN_FLD_NAME is used to name the plan lists. Also, PIN_FLD_TYPE_STR can be 'new' or 'addon'.   Plan lists are created using the Pricing Tool or the load_plan_lists command line utility. The policy opcode PCM_OP_CUST_POL_GET_PLANS uses the plan lists. "
1     PIN_FLD_LABEL           STR [0] "Group object for Plan lists"
1     PIN_FLD_READ_ACCESS     STR [0] "Brand"
1     PIN_FLD_WRITE_ACCESS    STR [0] "Self"
