1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/plan"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "A plan packages what you are offering the customer (the service) with how you are charging them for it (the deal). The charge details are themselves defined in the products. It serves as a template for new or existing customer accounts.  For example, you might offer one service with two different ways of charging for it, each defined in a separate deal. When you create the plan, you choose which of the deals to include in the plan. In almost all cases, plans include services. By including services in plans, the customer creates their service login name and password when they register. The only time you might not include a service in a plan is if the plan contains only account-level products and deals. Plans further simplify the choices presented to customers. Typically, plans are used to register new customers. However, they can also be used to add services and deals to existing accounts."
