1     PIN_FLD_NAME            STR [0] "/service/vpdn"
1     PIN_FLD_DESCR           STR [0] "VPDN Service Object. This is designed for support of VPDN  solutions. This object is used to store certain attributes  that are needed to establish a VPDN session, like the  tunneling protocol and other information that the NAS  uses to set up a tunnel to the organization that the  user wants to connect to. This object is similar to the  /service/ip object and a VPDN solution can be implemented  using either one of these, but /service/vpdn is recommended  because this will allow the /service/ip storable object  to support the /account dialup function."
